  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed mansard roof extension by reason of its prominent siting, scale and form would form a dominant and discordant addition unacceptably interrupting the existing predominantly unaltered and legible front and rear roofline, would be visible from short to longer viewpoints from the surrounding public and private realm and would be harmful to the character and appearance of the host building, wider terrace setting and the Conservation Area.  The proposal is therefore contrary to policies D4 and HC1 of the London Plan 2021, policies CS8 and CS9 of the Core Strategy (2011), policies DM2.1 and DM2.3 of the Development Management Policies (2013), guidance in the Islington Urban Design Guide (2017), Islington's Conservation Area Design Guidelines & The NPPF 2019."
